# **Part 2**

## **Describe a happy event you organized.**

One happy event I organized was a small birthday celebration for one of my close friends during university. It happened last year, shortly before our final exams. At that time, everyone was under a lot of academic pressure, so I thought it would be nice to organize something relaxing and memorable to cheer him up.

The event itself wasn’t extremely large, but I still spent quite a lot of time preparing for it. I booked a small private room in a restaurant near our university and invited several of our close friends. I also helped prepare decorations, ordered a birthday cake, and even made a short video using photos and clips from our university life together. Since I’m relatively familiar with technology and editing software, I was mainly responsible for the planning and coordination.

A few of my classmates also helped me organise the event. Some of them contacted guests, while others prepared gifts and arranged the schedule. At first, we were a little worried because everyone was busy with assignments and exam preparation, so it was difficult to find a suitable time when everyone was free. However, in the end, things worked out surprisingly well.

What made the event particularly memorable was the atmosphere. My friend was genuinely surprised because he hadn’t expected anyone to organise something like that during such a stressful period. Everyone laughed a lot, shared memories, and spent a really enjoyable evening together. Honestly, I felt extremely satisfied and happy afterwards, not only because the event was successful, but also because it reminded me how important friendship and shared experiences are. I think organising events can sometimes be stressful, but seeing other people happy makes all the effort worthwhile.

---

## **中文翻译：**

我组织过的一次开心活动，是大学期间为一个好朋友举办的小型生日聚会。那是在去年期末考试前不久。当时大家学习压力都很大，所以我觉得组织一个轻松、难忘的活动能让他开心一点。

这个活动规模不算特别大，但我还是花了很多时间准备。我订了学校附近餐厅的一个包间，还邀请了几个关系很好的朋友。我还帮忙准备装饰、订蛋糕，甚至用大学生活中的照片和视频做了一个短片。因为我比较熟悉电脑和视频编辑，所以主要负责策划和协调。

我的几个同学也帮了很多忙。有的人负责联系朋友，有的人准备礼物、安排流程。刚开始我们有点担心，因为大家都在忙作业和复习考试，很难找到所有人都有空的时间。不过最后事情进行得 surprisingly well。

最让我难忘的是当时的氛围。我的朋友真的很惊喜，因为他完全没想到在那么忙的时候大家还会给他准备生日活动。大家一起聊天、回忆大学经历，气氛特别开心。活动结束后，我感到非常满足，因为不仅活动成功了，也让我意识到友情和共同回忆有多重要。我觉得组织活动虽然有时会很累，但看到别人开心，一切努力都值得。

